descript.abstract: This polygon data layer represents municipalities for Waukesha County, Wisconsin in 2013. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Waukesha_Municipalities_2013.gdb. [Boundaries for all municipalities within Waukesha County.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Definition of jurisdictional limits.]

procstep.procdesc: [There were two methods used to digitize the cadastral features in Waukesha County. Most of the eastern half of the county was completed by board digitizing section-based 1""=100' scale mylars. These mylars were constructed using USPLSS monuments and section lines, as well as various planimetric features, (pavement, structures and water features) as a base. Each section was then manually drafted using Subdivision Plats, Certified Survey Maps, Condominium Plats, Deeds of Record, and the County Tax Roll. The mylars were then registered and board digitized. COGO entry using distance and bearing was used for most of the western half of the county. Both methods were quality controlled by generating a series of seven color check plots. The features were checked for positional accuracy, as well as for adherence to the County's level/layering specification. (See ""Waukesha County Digital Cadastral Specifications"")]

horizpa.horizpar: [This data set was prepared to meet National Map Accuracy Standards for one-inch equals 100 feet scale mapping and for one-inch equals 200 feet scale mapping. Therefore, ninety percent of all well defined planimetric features in this data set are within either 3.3 feet (1"=100') or 6.6 feet (1"=200') of their true position.]
